In a speech delivered at the Buenos Aires Stock Exchange, Vice President Mike Pence emphasized the United States' commitment to Latin America and discussed the importance of economic growth, collective security, and protecting freedom and democracy in the region. He highlighted Argentina's economic reforms under President Mauricio Macri as a model for other countries in Latin America. Pence also addressed the crisis in Venezuela, calling for the restoration of democracy and pledging continued U.S. support for the Venezuelan people. He stressed the importance of working together with Latin American nations to address common challenges and promote prosperity and security in the region.